---
// SpecStudio Skills — dedicated landing page.
// Canonical campaign URL: specscore.md/ai/specstudio-skills/
// Per STRATEGY.md § Domain authority strategy: this is the mid-funnel
// surface where campaign links (articles, blog posts, social CTAs) point.
// Content follows the marketing draft at marketing/distribution/specstudio-skills-website-homepage.md
// Design matches the specscore.md homepage Astro app (paper-and-ink, same tokens).
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../../../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../../../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SpecStudio Skills — Specs your AI agent can actually follow."
  description="Free Claude Code plugin that turns vibe-coded prompts into structured, scored specs your agent reads before it writes a single line of code. Built on the open SpecScore protocol."
  canonical="https://specscore.md/ai/specstudio-skills/"
>
  <SiteHeader />

  <main>
    {/* ── Section 1: Hero ── */}
    <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
      <div class="hero__inner">
        <h1 id="hero-title" class="hero__headline">
          Specs your AI agent<br />can actually follow.
        </h1>
        <p class="hero__sub">
          SpecStudio Skills is a free Claude Code plugin that turns
          vibe-coded prompts into structured, scored specs your agent reads
          before it writes a single line of code. Built on the open
          <a class="xref" href="https://specscore.md">SpecScore</a> protocol.
        </p>
        <div class="hero__install">
<pre class="terminal"><span class="prompt">$</span> /plugin marketplace add specscore/ai-marketplace
<span class="prompt">$</span> /plugin install specstudio@specscore</pre>
        </div>
        <p class="hero__demo-link">
          <a href="#demo" class="xref">Watch the 60-second demo ↓</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Section 2: Demo ── */}
    <section class="section" id="demo" aria-labelledby="demo-title">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 id="demo-title" class="section-title">
          From vibe to scored spec, in 60 seconds.
        </h2>

        <div class="demo-placeholder">
          <div class="terminal-frame">
            <div class="terminal-frame__head">
              <span class="terminal-frame__title">Claude Code</span>
              <span class="terminal-frame__hint">demo</span>
            </div>
<pre class="terminal terminal-frame__body"><span class="prompt">&gt;</span> /specstudio:ideate A password reset flow for our SaaS app.

<span class="dim">Refining idea...</span>
<span class="dim">Producing spec/ideas/password-reset.md</span>

<span class="prompt">&gt;</span> /specstudio:specify spec/ideas/password-reset.md

<span class="dim">Writing Feature spec...</span>
<span class="dim">spec/features/password-reset/README.md</span>

<span class="prompt">$</span> specscore lint spec/features/password-reset/
<span class="mark-pass">PASS</span>  Feature: password-reset
  <span class="mark-pass">PASS</span>  has title, status, and description
  <span class="mark-pass">PASS</span>  requirements have acceptance criteria
  <span class="mark-pass">PASS</span>  all AC IDs are unique
  <span class="mark-pass">PASS</span>  no orphan cross-references

<span class="mark-pass">Score: 92 / 100</span></pre>
          </div>
          <p class="demo-caption">
            No edit. No cuts. Blank Claude Code → install plugin → score a
            real spec → agent ships the right thing.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Section 3: The wedge ── */}
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="wedge-title">
      <div class="section-inner section-inner--prose">
        <h2 id="wedge-title" class="section-title">
          Why your agent keeps building the wrong thing.
        </h2>
        <p class="prose-p">
          Vibe-coded prompts work until they don't. The agent built half the
          feature. It misread the requirement. It invented an API call. It
          picked the wrong library. You re-prompt. You re-prompt again. By the
          third round you're typing the spec out longhand into the chat box
          anyway.
        </p>
        <p class="prose-p">
          The problem isn't the agent. It's that "build me a feature" is not a
          spec — it's a wish. Agents are stochastic. Wishes are
          stochastic-friendly. Specs are not.
        </p>
        <p class="prose-p">
          SpecStudio Skills gives you a workflow for writing specs your agent
          can actually parse: structured features, requirements, acceptance
          criteria, scored for completeness before the agent ever sees them.
          Same speed as vibe-coding, dramatically lower variance in the output.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Section 4: The pipeline ── */}
    <section class="section pipeline-section" aria-labelledby="pipeline-title">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 id="pipeline-title" class="section-title">
          Four commands. One pipeline.
        </h2>
        <p class="pipeline-intro">
          Install once, then run them in order — from raw idea to executable plan.
        </p>

        <div class="pipeline-grid">
          <div class="pipeline-card">
            <div class="pipeline-card__head">
              <span class="pipeline-card__cmd">/ideate</span>
            </div>
            <p class="pipeline-card__desc">
              Refine a raw idea through structured divergent and convergent
              thinking. Produces a lintable pre-spec one-pager.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="pipeline-card">
            <div class="pipeline-card__head">
              <span class="pipeline-card__cmd">/specify</span>
            </div>
            <p class="pipeline-card__desc">
              Turn an approved idea into a SpecScore Feature with requirements,
              acceptance criteria, and Given/When/Then blocks.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="pipeline-card">
            <div class="pipeline-card__head">
              <span class="pipeline-card__cmd">/plan</span>
            </div>
            <p class="pipeline-card__desc">
              Decompose a feature into an ordered list of tasks. Each task
              maps to one or more acceptance criteria.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="pipeline-card">
            <div class="pipeline-card__head">
              <span class="pipeline-card__cmd">/implement</span>
            </div>
            <p class="pipeline-card__desc">
              Execute the next task in the plan. One subagent per task,
              AC-traceable commits, staged diff for your approval.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Section 5: What's in the box ── */}
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="box-title">
      <div class="section-inner section-inner--prose">
        <h2 id="box-title" class="section-title">
          What's in the box.
        </h2>

        <h3 class="list-heading">Does:</h3>
        <ul class="feature-list feature-list--does">
          <li>Adds slash commands for the full SDD workflow: <code>/ideate</code>, <code>/specify</code>, <code>/plan</code>, <code>/implement</code>.</li>
          <li>Scores spec completeness and ambiguity before the agent sees the spec.</li>
          <li>Writes specs in the open SpecScore format — no proprietary extension.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="list-heading">Doesn't:</h3>
        <ul class="feature-list feature-list--doesnt">
          <li>Run the agent for you. The plugin is a workflow layer; the agent is still Claude.</li>
          <li>Phone home. Specs and scores stay local.</li>
          <li>Lock you in. If you uninstall, your specs are still valid Markdown and still scoreable by the <a class="xref" href="https://github.com/specscore/specscore">specscore</a> CLI.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="sibling-callout">
          Looking for the neutral CLI surface?
          <a class="xref" href="https://github.com/specscore/ai-plugin-specscore">ai-plugin-specscore</a>
          is the thin wrapper. SpecStudio Skills is the opinionated workflow on top.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Section 6: Open underneath ── */}
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="open-title">
      <div class="section-inner section-inner--prose">
        <h2 id="open-title" class="section-title">
          Built on the open SpecScore protocol.
        </h2>
        <p class="prose-p">
          SpecStudio Skills writes specs in
          <a class="xref" href="https://specscore.md">SpecScore</a>, an open
          standard. The format is human-readable Markdown. The schema is
          published. The CLI is open source. No vendor lock-in. If you ever
          leave SpecStudio, your specs come with you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  {/* ── Final CTA ── */}
  <section class="final-cta" aria-labelledby="cta-title">
    <div class="final-cta__inner">
      <h2 id="cta-title" class="final-cta__title">Try it.</h2>
      <div class="final-cta__install">
<pre class="terminal"><span class="prompt">$</span> /plugin marketplace add specscore/ai-marketplace
<span class="prompt">$</span> /plugin install specstudio@specscore</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="final-cta__note">
        Free for public and open-source repositories. MIT-licensed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ── Footer ── */}
  <footer class="page-footer">
    <div class="page-footer__inner">
      <div class="page-footer__col page-footer__brand">
        <a href="/" class="wordmark" aria-label="SpecScore home">
          <span class="wordmark__clef" aria-hidden="true">&#x1D11E;</span>
          <span class="wordmark__name">SpecScore.md</span>
        </a>
        <p class="page-footer__tagline">
          An open standard for specifications, requirements,
          and acceptance criteria.
        </p>
        <p class="page-footer__copyright">
          &copy; 2026 SpecScore contributors. MIT license.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="page-footer__col">
        <h4 class="page-footer__heading">SpecStudio Skills</h4>
        <ul class="page-footer__list">
          <li><a href="https://github.com/specscore/specstudio-skills">GitHub</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/specscore/specstudio-skills/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md">Changelog</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/specscore/specstudio-skills/blob/main/LICENSE">License: MIT</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="page-footer__col">
        <h4 class="page-footer__heading">Ecosystem</h4>
        <ul class="page-footer__list">
          <li><a href="https://specscore.md">SpecScore</a> — the open standard</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/specscore/ai-plugin-specscore">ai-plugin-specscore</a> — thin CLI wrapper</li>
          <li><a href="https://specscore.studio">SpecScore Studio</a> — web viewer</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Hero ── */
  .hero {
    padding: var(--space-7) var(--space-3) var(--space-6);
    background: var(--cream);
  }
  .hero__inner {
    max-width: var(--max-prose);
    margin: 0 auto;
    animation: fade-in 600ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 0.61, 0.36, 1) both 180ms;
  }
  .hero__headline {
    font-size: var(--fs-hero);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.04;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .hero__sub {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .hero__install {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .hero__demo-link {
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    color: var(--mid-ink);
  }

  @keyframes fade-in {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  /* ── Section titles ── */
  .section-title {
    font-size: var(--fs-h2);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  /* ── Demo ── */
  .demo-placeholder {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }
  .demo-caption {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    color: var(--mid-ink);
  }

  /* Terminal frame (shared with homepage AiSkills pattern) */
  .terminal-frame {
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    background: var(--surface);
  }
  .terminal-frame__head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.875rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    background: var(--cream-2);
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .terminal-frame__title { color: var(--graphite); font-weight: 700; }
  .terminal-frame__hint  { color: var(--mid-ink); }
  .terminal-frame__body  { border: none !important; }

  /* ── Wedge (prose sections) ── */
  .prose-p {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .prose-p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ── Pipeline grid ── */
  .pipeline-section {
    background: var(--cream-2);
  }
  .pipeline-intro {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .pipeline-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }
  .pipeline-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding: var(--space-3);
  }
  .pipeline-card__head {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .pipeline-card__cmd {
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .pipeline-card__desc {
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .pipeline-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .pipeline-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  /* ── What's in the box ── */
  .list-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--fs-h3);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .list-heading:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .feature-list {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3) 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .feature-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .feature-list li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .feature-list code {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .sibling-callout {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--hairline);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* ── Final CTA ── */
  .final-cta {
    background: var(--cream-2);
    padding: var(--space-7) var(--space-3);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }
  .final-cta__inner {
    max-width: var(--max-prose);
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .final-cta__title {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.2vw, 3.2rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }
  .final-cta__install {
    display: inline-block;
    text-align: left;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .final-cta__note {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
  }

  /* ── Page footer (per-page variant matching the specstudio-skills draft) ── */
  .page-footer {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-3) var(--space-5);
  }
  .page-footer__inner {
    max-width: var(--max-content);
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }
  .page-footer__brand .wordmark {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .page-footer__tagline {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    max-width: 36ch;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .page-footer__copyright {
    color: var(--pale-ink);
    font-size: 0.825rem;
    font-family: var(--font-code);
  }
  .page-footer__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .page-footer__list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }
  .page-footer__list a {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 120ms ease;
  }
  .page-footer__list a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--ink);
  }
  .page-footer__list a:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--ink-blue);
    outline-offset: 2px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .page-footer__inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
    .page-footer__brand {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
    }
  }
</style>
